B. An IRCA, to be eligible shall fulfil the following requirements namely:

1. A minimum of five years experience in the field of prevention of Alcoholism as substance (drug) abuse; 
1. Delivered comprehensive treatment services for people with alcoholism and drug dependence which includes follow-up and providing opportunities for rehabilitation; 
1.

Established or networked or provided a referral to vocational rehabilitation centres towards the rehabilitation of addicts and their families; 
1. Provided and continues to provide outreach services including conducting camps in villages and in small towns; 
1. Made and continues to make use of involvement of the community towards prevention of addiction, rehabilitation of treated addicts and dealing with issues related to stigma and discrimination; 
1. Outstanding ability towards documentation and periodical evaluation and making appropriate changes based on the feedback; 
